HEADWORD: Amia
<hw>Am"i*a</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr. <?/
a kind of tunny.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of fresh-water
ganoid fishes, exclusively confined to North America; called
<altname>bowfin</altname> in Lake Champlain, <altname>dogfish</altname>
in Lake Erie, and <altname>mudfish</altname> in South Carolina, etc. See
<er>Bowfin</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

